    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "The debug builds of CPython enable many nice assertions to find bugs in C extensions. It would be nice to have at least one debug build (say, of the latest CPython release series) included in our CI target platforms.\r\n\r\n1) find out how to install a CPython debug build in GH Actions\r\n2) add a matrix config entry in the [`ci.yml`](https://github.com/cython/cython/blob/master/.github/workflows/ci.yml) workflow file",
    "closed_at": null,
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "NumPy uses the one that comes with Ubuntu. Maybe there is a better way?\r\n```\r\nsudo apt install python3-dbg python3-dev python3-setuptools\r\npython3-dbg -m venv venv\r\nsource venv/bin/activate\r\n```",
